Jenkins files are used in Jenkins to automate the process like tes, build, deploy etc.
####In Jenkins, a Shared Library is a version-controlled collection of Groovy scripts that allow you to reuse code, scripts, and common functionality across multiple pipelines


@Library('Shared')_
pipeline{
    agent { label 'dev-server'}

    stages{
        stage("Code clone"){
            steps{
                sh "whoami"
            clone("https://github.com/---------------------","main")
            }
        }
        stage("Code Build"){
            steps{
            dockerbuild("notes-app","latest")
            }
        }
        stage("Push to DockerHub"){
            steps{
                dockerpush("dockerHubCreds","notes-app","latest")
            }
        }
        stage("Deploy"){
            steps{
                deploy()
            }
        }

    }
}


